                    Section 3 – Installing Nmap and Cloud Labs
1 - Goals and Learning Objectives
What the student is expected to learn from the section

2 - How to Install Nmap
NMap is available for most platforms
To install on Linux
  - sudo apt-get install nmap
The instructor recommends running NMap from Kali Linux
  - https://www.kali.org/downloads/
  - It is a pen-testing tool based on Debian
  - You can use VMware or Virtual Box to install on a virtual machine
Some versions of Linux come with NMap pre-installed
  - nmap --version at the command line to check to see if it is installed
  - Preinstalled versions maybe older so will need updating
  - There are source code packages available which can be used to build an install
    - These are often quicker etc because they are built closer to your machine specs

